@startuml class_diagram

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam classFontStyle Bold

package "src" {
    class Calculator {
        +add(a, b) : float|int
        +subtract(a, b) : float|int
        +multiply(a, b) : float|int
        +divide(a, b) : float|int
        +factorial(n: int) : int
        +square(x) : float
        +cube(x) : float
        +square_root(x) : float
        +cube_root(x) : float
        +power(base, exp) : float
        +log(x) : float
        +ln(x) : float
    }

    class "__main__" as Main <<module>> {
        +main() : None
    }

    class "__init__" as Init <<module>> {
        __all__ : list
    }
}

package "tests" {
    class "test_calculator" as TestModule <<module>> {
        +calc() : Calculator  <<fixture>>
        ' 76 tests covering all 12 operations
        +test_add_*()
        +test_subtract_*()
        +test_multiply_*()
        +test_divide_*()
        +test_factorial_*()
        +test_square_*()
        +test_cube_*()
        +test_square_root_*()
        +test_cube_root_*()
        +test_power_*()
        +test_log_*()
        +test_ln_*()
    }
}

Main --> Calculator : instantiates
Init ..> Calculator : re-exports
TestModule --> Calculator : tests via fixture

note right of Calculator
  Division: delegates to Python "/" operator.
  ZeroDivisionError raised by runtime when b == 0.
  factorial: iterative; rejects bool/float/non-int
  (TypeError) and negatives (ValueError).
  square_root: raises ValueError for x < 0.
  cube_root: handles negatives via -(abs(x)^(1/3)).
  log: base-10 via math.log10; raises ValueError for x <= 0.
  ln: natural log via math.log; raises ValueError for x <= 0.
  power: returns base ** exp (no domain restriction).
  Imports: math
end note

@enduml
